reviews_data.review_text: Great place to take a date, friend, or family to enjoy delicious beverages & cats/kittens companionship

Always an absolute joy being here! The staff is superb and the cats are always absolutely adorable and the sweetest! Great atmosphere and pricing for cat times and the snacks are the bomb! Definitely love being so close to a gem like this 😻
Best place to spend an afternoon! Love visiting the cats and the coffee is delicious!

Cool little place.  I love the idea of having the cat room (sounds like you should expect to make reservations based on high demand).  I would never have though in a million years people would pay $7/person for 1/2 hour to play with cats.  LOL  Good for them though for figuring that out.

Prices are reasonable.  Staff is nice.  They serve alcohol as well.

It has a nice patio seating area outside.

One thing that would be nice would be to add some more natural light inside.  It's a little dark.  Otherwise, the environment is quite nice.

Staff members were super friendly and they take good care of the cats. The cat room was very clean and full of cat toys. They also provide a private room for the cats if they ever want to rest alone, which is a really thoughtful design.

I love visiting Mac Tabby because of three things:

1. They have a great and inspiring mission
2. They have delicious coffee
3. They have the funniest and sweetest cats that love getting human attention

This is such a gem to have in Downtown Concord and suggest that anyone reading this review should go pay them a visit.  Even if you think you’re a “dog person”, this experience will change your opinion very quickly because it’s so natural and therapeutic. Already excited to come back to visit!
Cool place ,love the kitty's

Nice vibe to the cafe, this location wasn’t too packed to where my girlfriend and I could relax while drinking our coffee then enjoying time with the cats! They have plenty of toys and sensory items to get the cat’s attention. Cool place!
I LOVED our experience here today. All the employees were wonderful and so friendly:) we will definitely be back!
Absolutely LOVE IT!!!! Would highly recommend! Super friendly cats.

I wonder if they might increase the child age to 10, 11, 12 years and up… and / or post a list of rules in the cat room. Recently there have been MULTIPLE kids chasing and scaring the cats, aggressively flinging toys across the room, and grabbing at cats to pick them up 😬 And of course their parents / grown ups do nothing about it.

Sometimes we leave the room early because kids are being obnoxious and unsupervised. It’s overstimulating for people AND cats, and it ruins the fun.

Please educate kids before they enter the cat room to setup their expectations. This is NOT a playground for you to run and scream and pull out the furniture. Some cats want to sleep and be calm. If you are slow and gentle they are more likely to come to you. And PLEASE do not lunge or grab at them 😢

Love the staff here. A great fixture in the Concord community! I find that this one is much easier to park and walk to than the one in Noda.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Pink! Thank you for your feedback. We definitely go over rules before entering especially with kids! We also feel as you do, and wish the parents would be more mindful. Our team does their best but sometimes is called to the cafe side or can't be in the room the full hour for whatever reason - so PLEASE come and get us if you feel uncomfortable! We will definitely remedy the situation in the cat room. We remind kids that our job is to protect the animals and if we feel they may be in danger the children are asked to step out. This info is also in the waiver that is signed before entering. We don't want anyone to have a stressful time so please just let us know the next time you visit if you feel you need our assistance for a more peaceful experience. We would appreciate it greatly! Thank you!

Who pays to sit with cats? Went in to pick up a friend. Staff became stressed because I did not exit quickly enough.
Edit: No signage regarding rules visibly posted and the staff could have been friendlier about the situation. I recommend volunteering at a local animal shelter if you need a pet fix.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Jim! A lot of people pay to pet cats. They are CATS. People love those little perfect creatures! The fee to enter helps us keep a roof over their heads and adoption numbers climbing. We weren't stressed, you just walked into the cat space that people did in fact pay, which you didn't, and you let yourself in which means a cat could have gotten out... so our team came over to let you know that you shouldn't have just walked in to the cat room. We have policies and procedures in place to protect the animals and the serenity of the humans who are visiting with them. We allow patrons in / out on the half hour mark under staff supervision so our cats stay protected in the space they belong in. We understand that you may not have realized that, but it wasn't personal, our team was following safety procedures and rules of the cafe. Next time you visit, please hang on the cafe side only and our team will escort your friends out after their session is over (or pay to enter with them! reviews_data.review_text:
I went to Mac Tabby on a Sunday shortly after they opened and would highly recommend it! The cafe is cute and houses an extensive menu, making this a great spot to come for a great cup of coffee, not just the cats! As a lounge, the cats were a mix of active and sleepy, which was fine by me. All were kind and receptive to petting.

Unfortunately, the group in the cat lounge with us consisted of two children who were rowdy, and they made the experience less than enjoyable. My boyfriend and I were looking forward to spending some time with kitties, and instead we spent 30 minutes with kids who were jumping around (one of which consistently jumped in front of the cats) and dangling the toys in an attempt to make the kittens "do a backflip", which was stressful. In the future, it would be nice to see them have a supervised, children-only room, or different hours reserved just for adults. Despite that, I still rate my visit a 5/5, because this is not the cafe's doing, but the children! Your experience could be entirely different.

Again, I don't hold this against the cafe at all, nor do I the workers, as they were all extremely friendly, but if you're looking to avoid children and relax during your visit, consider coming during the week. I will be back, but likely during a weekday where I'm less likely to share the lounge with kids who are throwing toys onto the air vent to get a cat to jump down.

I’m so impressed with this Cat Cafe; I am have traveled the country to visit different cat cafes, and I have also worked at one. This is the best cat cafe I’ve ever visited!! This is my second time coming here and I’m consistently impressed.

The coffee is amazing and has so many fun flavors and seasonal options. I got the huckleberry latte and it was so yummy!

The cat lounge is very cute and has lots of art and decor that’s perfect for a photo op. It’s very very clean in there and doesn’t smell like cat whatsoever. Most cat cafes I’ve been to have at least a little cat smell, but not here. I also like that they have plastic furniture with comfy removable cushions and blankets— easy to remove and sanitize so you know this place is clean.

The environment is also very cozy and chill; dimly lit with colorful Christmas lights and rustic decor. It’s a space I would hang out in regardless of the cats.

The cats themselves are very friendly and cuddly! They have 12 adoptable cats from the humane society and they are all very well taken care of and seem very happy. I would recommend coming here to support their amazing cause— getting cats off the streets and out of scary noisy shelters fosters a space for the cats to be happy, calm, social, and really show their personality. If you’re looking to adopt a cat, absolutely get one from here!

Can’t wait to visit again in the future! Thank you from Salt Lake City, Utah!!

reviews_data.review_text: I really enjoyed my visit at Mac Tabby Cat Cafe in Concord, NC.  The location is great with easy access to parking. reviews_data.review_text: This place is welcoming and gorgeously decorated. I will absolutely be going back. The peanut butter banana smoothie was so so good. The rules are age 7+ and I think that is a good idea as the cats need to have safe rules in place so they are safe. The set up of maximizing this quaint building is done very well. There is a good bit of spaced out seating for groups of 2-4, ~5 parties of that or so. I am excited for drinks from southern strain brewery from Concord and other small businesses to be at this establishment for a relaxing night out. The front porch is a great place to relax in the shade outside. You enter the building through the side of the building. You get to the front porch by the outside gate. I LOVED our experience here today. All the employees were wonderful and so friendly:) we will definitely be back!
Absolutely LOVE IT!!!! Would highly recommend! Super friendly cats.

I wonder if they might increase the child age to 10, 11, 12 years and up… and / or post a list of rules in the cat room. Recently there have been MULTIPLE kids chasing and scaring the cats, aggressively flinging toys across the room, and grabbing at cats to pick them up 😬 And of course their parents / grown ups do nothing about it.

Sometimes we leave the room early because kids are being obnoxious and unsupervised. It’s overstimulating for people AND cats, and it ruins the fun.

Please educate kids before they enter the cat room to setup their expectations. This is NOT a playground for you to run and scream and pull out the furniture. Some cats want to sleep and be calm. If you are slow and gentle they are more likely to come to you. And PLEASE do not lunge or grab at them 😢

Edit: No signage regarding rules visibly posted and the staff could have been friendlier about the situation. I recommend volunteering at a local animal shelter if you need a pet fix.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Jim! A lot of people pay to pet cats. They are CATS. People love those little perfect creatures! The fee to enter helps us keep a roof over their heads and adoption numbers climbing. We weren't stressed, you just walked into the cat space that people did in fact pay, which you didn't, and you let yourself in which means a cat could have gotten out... so our team came over to let you know that you shouldn't have just walked in to the cat room. We have policies and procedures in place to protect the animals and the serenity of the humans who are visiting with them. We allow patrons in / out on the half hour mark under staff supervision so our cats stay protected in the space they belong in. We understand that you may not have realized that, but it wasn't personal, our team was following safety procedures and rules of the cafe. Next time you visit, please hang on the cafe side only and our team will escort your friends out after their session is over (or pay to enter with them! The cafe is cute and houses an extensive menu, making this a great spot to come for a great cup of coffee, not just the cats! My boyfriend and I were looking forward to spending some time with kitties, and instead we spent 30 minutes with kids who were jumping around (one of which consistently jumped in front of the cats) and dangling the toys in an attempt to make the kittens "do a backflip", which was stressful. In the future, it would be nice to see them have a supervised, children-only room, or different hours reserved just for adults. Despite that, I still rate my visit a 5/5, because this is not the cafe's doing, but the children! Your experience could be entirely different.

Again, I don't hold this against the cafe at all, nor do I the workers, as they were all extremely friendly, but if you're looking to avoid children and relax during your visit, consider coming during the week.
